\begin_inset Formula $\mathfrak{p}$
\end_inset

 of 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

, the fiber of 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi\colon Y\to X$
\end_inset

 over 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathfrak{p}$
\end_inset

, denoted 
\begin_inset Formula $Y_{\mathfrak{p}}$
\end_inset

, is the pullback of 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi\colon Y\to X$
\end_inset

 with respect to the morphism 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{\mathfrak{p}}\colon\mathrm{Spec}(\kappa(\mathfrak{p}))\to X$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\varepsilon_{\mathfrak{p}}$
\end_inset

 is the morphism which corresponds to the 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

-algebra homomorphism 
\begin_inset Formula $A\to\kappa(\mathfrak{p})$
\end_inset

.
 In particular, 
\begin_inset Formula $Y_{\mathfrak{p}}$
\end_inset

 is an affine 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

-scheme and the 
\begin_inset Formula $\Bbbk$
\end_inset

-algebra which corresponds to 
\begin_inset Formula $Y_{\mathfrak{p}}$
\end_inset

